When parasitic mite densities are high, the effect on collembolan populations could be significant (
Greenslade & Southcott, 1980
). In our population the mean intensity of infestation is 1 , although several Collembola bear two mites. The prevalence, that is, number of individuals of a host species infested divided by the number of hosts examined (
Margolis et al , 1982
), is around 10 %. The relationship between parasite and host size is approximately 3 : 1 .
